Q.7 Stock buy and sell Multiple Times -> 
Problem Statement , We have given Stock prices where we can sell the buy and sell the share multiple times 
* (According to ShareMarket rules like if We buy share on t0 and sell the share on t2 then we can never buy 
 on the price of t0 , we can only buy on t2 Basic---> )T2 will decide the price for next share.... 

like an array contins share price  -> 100,180 ,260 ,310 , 40 , 535 , 695 . 
if we buy on t0 nd sell on t1 then we can only do 1 things--
 1)  we can buy on t1 , we can sell on next t2,t3,t4 we never came back and buy t1 or sell t1.

* Approach-> 
we traverse a loop idx =1 -> and check if(arr[i]>arr[i-1] , prifit+=arr[i]-arr[i-1]; nd return profit;

// code-> class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int arr[]) {
        // code here
        int profit = 0;
        for(int i=1;i<arr.length;i++){
            if(arr[i]>arr[i-1]){
                profit+=arr[i]-arr[i-1];
            }
        }
        return profit;
    }
}
T.c-> O(n)  

Q.8. Stock buy and sell and return maximum profit (One Trajection allow) 
Approach -> initialize mxProfit = 0 ; minSoFar = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
loop i =0 to n-1 nd update minSoFar = Math.min(minSoFar,arr[i])
mx = Math.max(mx,arr[i]-minSoFar);
return mx;

code->>
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] arr) {
        // Code here
        int minSoFar = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int mx = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++){
            minSoFar = Math.min(arr[i],minSoFar);
            mx = Math.max(mx,arr[i]-minSoFar);
        }
        return mx;
    }
}

T.C-> O(n) 

